<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html lang="en" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
<head>
<title>JC/CCMAXLEN - Maximum length of cost code (defaults to 10)</title>
</head>
<body>
<div class="param_id">
<span class="parameter">JC/CCMAXLEN - </span> Maximum length of cost code (defaults to 10)
</div>
<div class="param_def">
<p><p>This allows you to set the maximum length of the cost code.  This can be between 8 and 16 characters. The default is 10.</p></p>
<p><p class="warningheader">WARNING</p>
<div class="warning">Cost codes that are longer than 10 characters may be truncated when displayed in <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../../Resources/Snippets/Coinsplus.flsnp"/>. For this reason, we <strong>strongly advise</strong> that you only set the maximum length to greater than 10 if you are <strong>only</strong> using <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../../Resources/Snippets/coinsoa.flsnp"/>.</div>
<p class="noteheader">NOTE</p>
<div class="note">The parameter <span class="parameter">CCMAXLEN </span>is currently ignored if the company parameter <span class="parameter">COMPLOC </span>is set to <span class="userselect">USA</span>.</div></p>
<p>
<MadCap:relatedTopics target="_self" style="mc-label: Related Parameter ;mc-help-control-display: list;"><MadCap:relatedTopic src="../camaxlen.htm/jc_camaxlen.htm" /></MadCap:relatedTopics>
</p>
</div>
</body>
</html>
